The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for civil engineering tasks, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also focuses on the use of Amazon Mechanical Turk, which is a platform for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper discusses the training and tutorials provided to the workers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the concerns over the quality of data and analysis, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for problem-solving tasks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
